always shared. the price can be quite low, costing only a few dozen renminbi. officially a zhusu should not provide a room to a foreigner, but many times the caretaker is eager to get a client and will be willing to rent to anyone. there are never any english signs advertising a zhusu, so if you can't read chinese you may have to print out the characters for your hunt. security in zhusu's is sketchy, so this option is not recommended if you have valuables with you. massage shops, saunas, and spas: spa costs vary but can be as low 